# Git Workflow Guide

## Initial Setup

```bash
# Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/negij5675-ops/cricket-tournament-website.git
cd cricket-tournament-website

# Set up git config
git config --global user.name "Your Name"
git config --global user.email "your.email@example.com"
```

## Branch Naming Convention

```
feature/feature-name          # New feature
bugfix/bug-name              # Bug fix
hotfix/critical-issue        # Critical production fix
refactor/refactor-name       # Code refactoring
docs/documentation-update    # Documentation
```

## Development Workflow

### 1. Create Feature Branch

```bash
# Update main branch
git checkout main
git pull origin main

# Create feature branch
git checkout -b feature/tournament-management
```

### 2. Make Changes

```bash
# Make your changes
# Edit files...

# Check status
git status

# Stage changes
git add .
# Or add specific files
git add backend/models/Tournament.js

# Commit with clear message
git commit -m "feat: add tournament creation functionality"
```

### 3. Push to Remote

```bash
git push origin feature/tournament-management
```

### 4. Create Pull Request

1. Go to GitHub repository
2. Click "Compare & pull request"
3. Add description of changes
4. Request reviewers
5. Merge after approval

### 5. Update Local Main

```bash
git checkout main
git pull origin main
```

## Commit Message Format

Follow conventional commits:

```
<type>(<scope>): <subject>

<body>

<footer>
```

### Examples

```
feat(auth): add JWT authentication
fix(tournament): resolve date validation issue
refactor(player): simplify statistics calculation
docs: update API documentation
test(match): add match controller tests
```

### Types
- **feat**: New feature
- **fix**: Bug fix
- **refactor**: Code refactoring
- **style**: Code style changes
- **test**: Test additions
- **docs**: Documentation
- **chore**: Build/dependency updates

## Useful Git Commands

```bash
# View commit history
git log --oneline

# See changes in current branch
git diff main

# Unstage changes
git restore --staged filename

# Discard local changes
git checkout -- filename

# Rename branch
git branch -m old-name new-name

# Delete branch
git branch -d branch-name
git push origin --delete branch-name

# Merge branch
git merge feature/tournament-management

# Rebase (keep history clean)
git rebase main

# View remote branches
git branch -r

# Fetch latest changes
git fetch origin

# Stash changes (save for later)
git stash
git stash pop
```

## Conflict Resolution

```bash
# If conflicts occur during merge/rebase
# 1. Edit conflicted files
# 2. Mark as resolved
git add resolved-file.js

# 3. Continue merge/rebase
git merge --continue
# or
git rebase --continue
```

## .gitignore

Make sure these are in .gitignore:

```
node_modules/
.env
.env.local
.DS_Store
*.log
build/
dist/
```

## Good Practices

1. ✅ Make small, focused commits
2. ✅ Write clear commit messages
3. ✅ Pull before pushing
4. ✅ Create feature branches
5. ✅ Don't commit .env files
6. ✅ Review code before pushing
7. ✅ Use pull requests for review
8. ✅ Keep main branch stable

## Emergency: Undo Recent Commits

```bash
# Undo last commit (keep changes)
git reset --soft HEAD~1

# Undo last commit (discard changes)
git reset --hard HEAD~1

# Revert a published commit
git revert commit-hash
```

---

For more Git help: https://git-scm.com/doc
